| Nmap Switch         | Function                                                                                                                                     | Advantages / Disadvantages                                                                                           |
|---------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| -sS                 | TCP SYN stealth scan, half-open scanning (never completes TCP connection, identifies port state)                                             | Requires privileged access to the NIC                                                                                |
| -sT                 | TCP connect scan. If privileged access is not available, Nmap uses this instead of -sS and uses OS to scan.                                  | Less stealthy                                                                                                        |
| -sN                 | null scan, header bit to zero                                                                                                                | Only host discovery                                                                                                  |
| -sF                 | FIN packet (end connection), for FIN scans                                                                                                   | bypass filtering, but potential open/closed port false positives                                                     |
| -sI                 | TCP Idle scanning, can use a zombie host to disguise the identity of the source host (your host) and proxy nmap requests via the zombie host | masquerades requests with existing hosts, but takes much longer than other scans                                     |
| -sP                 | Ping scan                                                                                                                                    | quick, but limited information                                                                                       |
| -sX                 | FIN, PSH, and URG flags XMAS attack                                                                                                          | can bypass certain firewalls and packet filtering systems, but results cannot discern between filtered vs open ports |
| -sU                 | scan UDP scan                                                                                                                                | fast, but takes a long time                                                                                          |
| -sW                 | TCP Window Scan                                                                                                                              | improves on ACK scan to better discern open ports, (scan can show wrong results though)                              |
| -p                  | specifies port range (can also include --exclude-ports to remove ports)                                                                      | n/a                                                                                                                  |
| -PS <PortList>      | TCP SYN ping                                                                                                                                 | probe other ports other than the default HTTP/HTTPS ones, checks if hosts online only though                         |
| -T<0-5>             | Increase the scan speed with a higher number                                                                                                 | disadvantage is potential increased probability of detection with a faster scan                                      |
| --traceroute        | option to record the path to an IP target address. Zenmap can display the network topology.                                                  | can be speedy and fast                                                                                               |
| -PT                 | separate lists of TCP ports                                                                                                                  | n/a                                                                                                                  |
| -PU                 | separate lists of UDP ports                                                                                                                  | n/a                                                                                                                  |
| -sV                 | version detection                                                                                                                            | Limited to versioning                                                                                                |
| -O                  | OS detection                                                                                                                                 | Fast, but limited to OS detection                                                                                    |
| -sO                 | IP Protocol scan (uses what protocols are supported by the target machine-- TCP, ICMP, IGMP, etc.)                                           | Good way to check if host is online via multiple methods, but takes longer                                           |
| -A                  | OS detection, traceroute, version detection, script scanning                                                                                 | Complete scan, but takes longer                                                                                      |
| -v                  | Verbosity level                                                                                                                              | More v's for more information, but can considerably increase output and noise                                        |
| NO FLAGS            | by default, uses a TCP SYN scan                                                                                                              | n/a                                                                                                                  |
| without privileges  | (e.g., root or SYSTEM) will use a TCP connect scan                                                                                           | Less stealthy                                                                                                        |
| --scan-delay <Time> | Nmap probes over a significant amount of time.                                                                                               | Defeats IDSs. Host discovery is a lengthy process. Configure delays using a timing template.                         |
| --randomize-hosts   | selects hosts randomly                                                                                                                       | Evades IDSs, lengthy, but good for large networks                                                                    |
| -d                  | decoy source IP addresses                                                                                                                    | enhances stealth                                                                                                     |
| -f or â€“mtu          | splits the TCP header of each probe between multiple IP datagrams.                                                                           | Harder for IDS to analyze and enhances stealth.                                                                      |
| -sC                 | default script scan                                                                                                                          | automate scanning, uses default scan                                                                                 |
| --script <path>     | script scan                                                                                                                                  | automate scanning                                                                                                    |
